Date: 0/0/1982
Source: Collins Concise English Dictionary
Author:
Vol / Page: 749
Edition:
Quote: nark Brit. & N.Z. sl. ~ n. 1. an informer or spy:  copper's nark. 2. someone who complains in an irritating or whining manner. vb. 3. (tr.) to annoy, upset, or irritate. 4. (intr.) to inform or spy, esp. for the police. 5. (intr.) to complain irritatingly. [C19: prob. < Romany nak nose]
Notes: [1986 NZPOD 499; 1985 Collins NZ Compact Dict. 323]
